sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1026009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A rationally designed promoter negative regulated by CcaR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: By fusing G-box, a region that CcaR binds, with the constitutive promoter, BBa_J23107, we devised a promoter that is constitutive without active CcaR (the transcription factor in green light sensor system, CcaS-CcaR-PcpcG2), but be inhibited when CcaR is activated by green light.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We discovered a segment around the -35 region of BBa_J23107 that is almost identical to G-box, the binding region of CcaR on PcpcG2. So we put the G-box onto this exact region, between -35 region and -10 region of the original promoter. Therefore, we expect that activated CcaR will bind and hinder RNA polymerase binding, and thus prevents transcription initialization.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hongyi WU
